A Professor of Soil Science, Abayomi Fasina, has emerged as the newly- elected Vice Chancellor of the Federal University of Oye-Ekiti (FUOYE). The Chairman of the Council, Dr. Mohammed Lawan, in a statement yesterday by the institutionâ€™s Deputy Director, Corporate Services, Mr. Adeyinka Ademuyiwa, announced the appointment. Fasina, the Deputy Vice Chancellor (Administration), prior to his appointment, emerged after beating other candidates. He is to take over from the outgoing Vice Chancellor, Prof. Kayode Soremekun, whose tenure ends on February 11.